AB  - The early exercise of capped variable rate loan commitments is formalized as the first passage time to a critical boundary in a compound option model. As early exercised commitment puts are American-style options, numerical procedures are used to obtain simulated values. It appears from the latter that the value of the early exercise premium is nontrivial and increasing with the terms to option expiry. Put values are also sensitive to the volatility of credit-market rates, as these affect the variance of the borrower's indebtedness value.
